description: This module provides a variety of linkout functions for the NGCHM API, enabling users to access external databases and resources related to genes, proteins, pathways, and other biological entities. It includes plugins for visualizing data in different formats, such as scatter plots and ideograms, and supports interaction with numerous bioinformatics tools and databases.

functions.name: openAmigo
functions.description: Opens a URL in the GeneOntology Amigo website using the first element of the provided names array.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of strings where the first element is used to construct the URL for the GeneOntology Amigo website.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchBioGPS
functions.description: This function searches for a given gene name on the BioGPS website and opens the search results in a new window.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used for the search query.

side_effects: Opens a new browser window or tab with the search results from BioGPS.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openSlideArchive
functions.description: Opens the Cancer Digital Slide Archive for a given patient ID by constructing a URL and forcing the browser to reload the page.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: An array of patient IDs, where the first ID is used to construct the URL.

side_effects: Forces the browser to reload the page.
Changes the current URL to the Cancer Digital Slide Archive for the specified patient ID.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openCBIOGenes
functions.description: Opens a URL in the cBioPortal with a specified list of genes for a given study.

parameters.name: genes
parameters.description: An array of gene names to be queried in the cBioPortal.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the cBioPortal with the specified genes and study ID.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openCBIOSamp
functions.description: Opens a cBioPortal case URL for a given study and case ID.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: An array containing case IDs. The first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openCBIOSampTCGA
functions.description: This function extracts the first 12 characters of the first element in the provided array of IDs and calls the openCBIOSamp function with this substring wrapped in an array.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: An array of strings representing IDs.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openCivicDB
functions.description: Opens the CivicDB website with the provided Entrez ID.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: An array containing Entrez IDs. The first ID in the array is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openCosmicGene
functions.description: Opens the COSMIC gene analysis page for the first gene name provided in the input array.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openDecipher
functions.description: Opens a URL in the Decipher database for the given gene name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openDepMap
functions.description: Opens a DepMap gene overview page for the given gene ID.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: An array containing gene IDs. The first element of the array is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchEnsemblForGene
functions.description: Searches for a gene in the Ensembl database using the provided gene names and species information.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names to search for. The first element is used for the search query.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the browser using the linkouts.openUrl method.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchEnsemblForTranscript
functions.description: Searches for a transcript in the Ensembl database using the provided transcript name and species.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array containing the transcript names to search for. The first element is used for the search.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the browser using the linkouts.openUrl method.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openFireBrowseGene
functions.description: Opens a FireBrowse webpage for a given gene name. This function constructs a URL to the FireBrowse website using the first gene name provided in the input array and opens it in a new window or tab.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the FireBrowse URL.

side_effects: Opens a new browser window or tab with the constructed FireBrowse URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openGdcGene
functions.description: Opens the GDC (Genomic Data Commons) portal for a specified gene using the provided label.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array containing gene labels, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openGdcCase
functions.description: Opens a GDC (Genomic Data Commons) case in a new browser tab using the provided case label.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array containing case labels, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

side_effects: Opens a new browser tab with the constructed GDC case URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchGeneCards
functions.description: This function searches for a gene in the GeneCards database using the first label provided in the labels array.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of strings where the first element is the gene name to search for in GeneCards.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openGenevisiblePeptide
functions.description: Opens a GeneVisible page for a given gene name in a new browser tab.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

side_effects: Opens a new browser tab with the GeneVisible page for the specified gene.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openGenevisibleHugo
functions.description: Opens a GeneVisible webpage for a given gene name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchGoogle
functions.description: This function performs a Google search using the provided selection array. It constructs a search URL by joining the elements of the selection array with a '+' character and opens this URL in a new frame using the linkouts.openUrl method.

parameters.name: selection
parameters.description: An array of strings that will be joined to form the search query.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in a frame using linkouts.openUrl.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchGoogleScholar
functions.description: This function constructs a Google Scholar search URL using the provided labels and opens it in a new window or tab.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of strings representing the search terms to be used in the Google Scholar query.

side_effects: Opens a new window or tab with the constructed Google Scholar search URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openGTExPortal
functions.description: Opens the GTEx Portal for a given gene ID in a new window or tab without using a frame.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: An array containing gene IDs, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openHGNCGene
functions.description: Opens the HGNC gene symbol report page for the first gene name provided in the input array.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to generate the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: viewIdeogramGene
functions.description: Opens the Ideogram viewer with a list of genes provided as input.

parameters.name: genes
parameters.description: An array of gene names to be visualized in the Ideogram viewer.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: viewIdeogramGene2
functions.description: This function opens a URL to the Ideogram Viewer with specified gene lists for rows and columns.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An object containing two arrays: 'Row' and 'Column', which represent lists of genes.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: viewIdeogramMIRNA
functions.description: This function processes a list of miRNA identifiers by removing the '.MIMAT' suffix from each identifier and then opens a URL to the Ideogram Viewer with the processed list of miRNA identifiers.

parameters.name: mir
parameters.description: An array of miRNA identifiers.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the 'ideogram' window.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: viewIdeogramMIRNA2
functions.description: Generates a URL to view miRNA ideograms based on provided labels and opens it in a new window.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An object containing 'Row' and 'Column' arrays of miRNA labels.

side_effects: Opens a new window with the generated URL.

returns.description: Does not return a value.

functions.name: openLinkedOmicsGene
functions.description: Opens a LinkedOmics gene page for the first gene name provided in the input array.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openLinkedOmicsIsoform
functions.description: Opens a LinkedOmics isoform page for a given protein name in a new browser tab or window.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of strings where the first element is the protein name to be used in the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openMavedbGene
functions.description: Opens a MaveDB search URL for a given gene name and species. Defaults to Homo sapiens if species is not specified.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array containing gene names, where the first element is used for the search.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: viewMiRBasePage
functions.description: This function takes an array of entity IDs (eids), extracts the miRNA ID from the first element, and opens a URL to the miRBase website for that specific miRNA.

parameters.name: eids
parameters.description: An array of entity IDs, where the first element contains the miRNA ID.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the browser using the linkouts.openUrl function.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openMSigDB
functions.description: Opens a URL to the MSigDB (Molecular Signatures Database) page for a given pathway name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of pathway names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: viewMupitG
functions.description: This function sorts and filters a list of gene names to remove duplicates, then opens a URL to the MuPIT Interactive tool for the first gene in the list.

parameters.name: genes
parameters.description: An array of gene names to be processed.

side_effects: Modifies the input array 'genes' by sorting and filtering it.

returns.description: Does not return a value.

functions.name: openMW
functions.description: Opens the Metabolomics Workbench website with a search query based on the first name in the provided list.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of names to be used for the search query. The first element is used in the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openRegno
functions.description: Opens a URL in a new window or tab based on the provided registration number (RegNo) from the first element of the names array. If the RegNo is empty, it alerts the user that no RegNo is available.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array where the first element is expected to be the registration number (RegNo) of a metabolite.

side_effects: Displays an alert if the RegNo is empty.
Opens a new window or tab with the constructed URL.

returns.description: Does not return a value.

functions.name: openPubchem
functions.description: Opens a PubChem URL for the given metabolite ID. If the ID is not available, it alerts the user.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array where the first element is expected to be the PubChem ID of the metabolite.

side_effects: Displays an alert if the PubChem ID is not available.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openRefmet
functions.description: Opens a URL in the Metabolomics Workbench site to search for the given name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of names where the first element is used for the search query.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openHMDB
functions.description: Opens the HMDB (Human Metabolome Database) webpage for a given metabolite name. If no name is provided, it alerts the user that no HMDB ID is available.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array containing the HMDB names. The first element is used to construct the URL.

side_effects: Displays an alert if the first element of the names array is an empty string.

returns.description: Does not return a value.

functions.name: openKEGG
functions.description: Opens a KEGG database URL for the given metabolite name. If the name is empty, it alerts the user that no KEGG ID is available.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of metabolite names, where the first element is used to construct the KEGG URL.

side_effects: Displays an alert if the first element in the names array is an empty string.

returns.description: Does not return a value.

functions.name: openChebi
functions.description: Opens a ChEBI webpage for the given metabolite name. If the name is empty, it alerts the user that no ChEBI name is available.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of metabolite names, where the first element is used to construct the ChEBI URL.

side_effects: Displays an alert if the first element of the names array is an empty string.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openMetacyc
functions.description: Opens a MetaCyc URL for the given metabolite name. If the name is empty, it alerts the user that no MetaCyc name is available.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array containing metabolite names, where the first element is the MetaCyc name.

side_effects: Displays an alert if the MetaCyc name is empty.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openClinVar
functions.description: Opens the ClinVar webpage for the specified gene name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the ClinVar URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openNCBIGenePage
functions.description: Opens the NCBI Gene page for a given gene name and species. The function constructs a URL based on the provided gene name and species, and then opens this URL in a new window or tab.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

side_effects: Opens a new window or tab with the constructed NCBI Gene URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openNCBIEntrezIDPage
functions.description: Opens the NCBI Gene page for the first Entrez ID in the provided list.

parameters.name: eids
parameters.description: An array of Entrez IDs, where the first ID in the array will be used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchNCBIDatabases
functions.description: Searches the NCBI databases for a given gene name and species, and opens the search results in a new window.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used for the search.

side_effects: Opens a new window with the NCBI search results.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openGEOAccession
functions.description: Opens a URL to the NCBI GEO database for the given accession ID.

parameters.name: aids
parameters.description: An array of accession IDs, where the first ID in the array will be used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchClinicalTrialsForOne
functions.description: This function searches for clinical trials related to the first label in the provided list by opening a URL to the ClinicalTrials.gov website.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of labels where the first label is used as the search term.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the browser.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchClinicalTrials
functions.description: This function constructs a search URL for clinical trials based on the provided labels and opens the URL in a new window or tab.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of strings representing the search terms to be used in the clinical trials search.

side_effects: Opens a new window or tab with the constructed URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: iQuery
functions.description: This function constructs a URL using a base URL and a list of GEO Accession identifiers, then opens this URL in a new window or tab labeled 'NDEx IQuery'.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of GEO Accession identifiers to be included in the URL.

side_effects: Opens a new browser window or tab with the constructed URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: iQuery2
functions.description: This function concatenates the Row and Column arrays from the labels object, removes duplicate values, and then calls the iQuery function with the resulting array.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An object containing Row and Column arrays to be concatenated and filtered for unique values.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openOLSVis
functions.description: Opens a URL in the OLSVis plugin using the first element of the provided names array.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of names where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openMDACCPathwayID
functions.description: Opens the MD Anderson Pathway Browser for the given gene name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openPathwaysBrowserGO
functions.description: Opens the Pathways Browser for a given Gene Ontology (GO) term using the first element in the provided names array.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of GO term names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openPeptideAtlas
functions.description: Opens the PeptideAtlas search page for the given gene name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used for the search.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchPubMedForOne
functions.description: This function searches PubMed for the first label in the provided array and opens the result in a new window without a frame.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of strings where the first element is used as the search term for PubMed.

side_effects: Opens a new window/tab with the PubMed search results.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchPubMedForAll
functions.description: This function constructs a PubMed search URL using the provided labels and opens the URL in a new frame.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of strings representing search terms to be combined with 'AND' for the PubMed search query.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in a frame using the linkouts.openUrl method.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchPubMedForAny
functions.description: Searches PubMed for any of the provided labels and opens the results in a new window.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of search terms to query in PubMed.

side_effects: Opens a new window with the PubMed search results.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openQuickGO
functions.description: Opens the QuickGO webpage for a given Gene Ontology (GO) term ID.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array where the first element is the GO term ID to be used in the QuickGO URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchAntibodyRegistry
functions.description: This function searches the Antibody Registry for a given label by opening a URL with the search query.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of labels to search for in the Antibody Registry. Only the first label in the array is used.

side_effects: Opens a URL in the browser to perform the search.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchSCICrunch
functions.description: This function constructs a URL to search for antibodies on the SCICrunch website using the first label provided in the labels array and opens this URL.

parameters.name: labels
parameters.description: An array of strings where the first element is used as the search query for SCICrunch.

side_effects: Opens a URL in the browser using the first label in the labels array as the search query.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: expandLinkOuts
functions.description: Expands the TCGA fields to allow any TCGA type longer than typeName by adding subtypes to the linkouts object. This function ensures that a subtype can be passed to any function expecting a supertype.
side_effects: Modifies the linkouts object by adding subtypes.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openTumorPortalGene
functions.description: Opens a TumorPortal page for the specified gene name in a new window or tab.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openUCSC
functions.description: Opens the UCSC Genome Browser at a specified genomic position.

parameters.name: posns
parameters.description: An array of genomic positions to be viewed in the UCSC Genome Browser. The first position in the array is used.

side_effects: Opens a new URL in the UCSC Genome Browser with the specified genomic position.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: openUniprot
functions.description: Opens the Uniprot webpage for the given gene name.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used to construct the Uniprot URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.

functions.name: searchVega
functions.description: This function searches for a given gene name on the Vega genome browser website. It constructs a URL using the provided gene name and the species attribute, then opens this URL in a new window or tab.

parameters.name: names
parameters.description: An array of gene names, where the first element is used for the search.

side_effects: Opens a new window or tab with the constructed URL.

returns.description: This function does not return a value.
